cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection and classification in images. Additionally, it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it uses convolutional neural networks to learn and exploit spatial relationships between objects. The paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it uses neural networks, and the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as object detection and classification is important in robotics applications.
